pallets, trays, racks, and shelves by hand, forklift, hoist or crane.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Load materials into vehicles and install strapping, bracing, or padding to prevent shifting or damage in transit.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Convey materials from storage or work sites to designated area.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Secure lifting attachments to materials and conveys load to destination or signal crane or hoisting operators to move load to destination.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Count, weigh, and record number of units of materials moved or handled on daily production sheet or computer while maintaining accurate inventory quantities.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Attach identifying tags or labels to materials; mark information on cases, bales, or other containers.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Stack or assemble materials into bundles and band bundles together.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Lift heavy objects by hand or with power hoist; clean work area.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Understanding and use of AS400 units to find location of parts, routing, product structure and parts availability.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Assist in receiving of parts from vendor and route truck.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Assist with cycle counts as needed.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Daily inspection and safe operation of forklift.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Operate industrial truck or electric hoist to assist in loading or moving materials and products.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Other duties may be assigned that require other qualifications, physical demands, and\u002For work environment.<\u002Fli>\n  <\u002Ful>\n  <div><\u002Fdiv>\n  <div>\n   <b><br> Preferred Skills and Qualifications:<\u002Fb>\n  <\u002Fdiv>\n  <ul>\n   <li> Previous forklift operator experience is required<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Ability to understand team concepts and be a strong team player<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Excellent written and verbal communication skills<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Ability to excel in fast-paced, high-pressure situations and be results-oriented<\u002Fli>\n New Hires will paint to plant standards prior to completion of program.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Proficient in paint skills for Great Plains and Land Pride products, preferred.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Demonstrated commitment to safety, and serves as a role model in safety behavior and wearing PPE in the plants.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> 3-5 years of spray painting experience. <p>Production Welder<\u002Fp> \n <p><\u002Fp>\n <p>At Great Plains our people make the difference, making our Company a great place to work and grow. If you are self-motivated, have a passion to succeed and value teamwork, we invite you to join our winning team. For over 40 years, Great Plains has been known as a world-class manufacturer of farm and landscaping equipment in Central Kansas and is home to 5 divisions, with over 1,500 dedicated employees. Now a Kubota company, Great Plains continues its dedication toward innovation and professional growth, while maintaining our 'family' culture and community values, perfect for building lasting careers while raising your family. Grow with us! Visit our Careers page at www.GreatPlainsMfg.com.<br> <\u002Fp> \n <p><\u002Fp>\n <p><b>SUMMARY<\u002Fb><\u002Fp> \n <p>Welds together metal components of products with electric arc-welding equipment by performing the following duties.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES <\u002Fb>include the following. Other duties may be assigned.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <ul>\n  <li>Follows all Great Plains and OSHA safety regulations and wears prescribed safety and protective equipment<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Obtains specified electrode and inserts electrode into portable holder or threads consumable electrode wire through portable welding gun.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Connects cables from welding unit to obtain amperage, voltage, slope, and pulse, as specified by Welding Supervisor.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Starts power supply to produce electric current.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Strikes (forms) arc which generates heat to melt and deposit metal from electrode\u002Fwire to work piece and join edges of work piece.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Manually guides electrode or gun along weld line, maintaining length of arc and speed of movement to form specified depth of fusion and bead, as judged from color of metal, sound of weld, and size of molten puddle.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Welds in flat, horizontal, vertical, or overhead positions.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Examines weld for bead size and other specifications.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Applies filler rod\u002Fwire manually to supply weld metal.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Cleans or degreases weld joint or work piece.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Repairs broken or cracked parts and fills holes.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Prepares broken parts for welding by grooving or scarfing surfaces.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Chips off excess weld, slag, and spatter.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Positions and clamps work pieces together or assembles them in jig or fixture.<\u002Fli> \n  <li>Tacks assemblies together.<\u002Fli>\n <\u002Ful>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITIES<\u002Fb><\u002Fp> \n <p>This job has no supervisory responsibilities.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>QUALIFICATIONS - To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and\u002For ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<\u002Fb><\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>EDUCATION and\u002For EXPERIENCE<\u002Fb><\u002Fp> \n <p>High school diploma or general education degree (GED) and one year experience and\u002For training; or equivalent combination of education and experience.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>LANGUAGE SKILLS<\u002Fb><\u002Fp> \n <p>Ability to read and interpret documents such as safety rules, operating and maintenance instructions, procedure manuals, work orders, and blueprints. Ability to write routine reports and correspondence. Ability to effectively present information in a one-on-one situation.<br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>MATHEMATICAL SKILLS<\u002Fb><\u002Fp> \n <p>Ability to add and subtract in all units of measure, using whole numbers, common fractions, and decimals.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>REASONING ABILITY<\u002Fb><\u002Fp> \n <p>Ability to apply common sense understanding to carry out instructions furnished in written, oral, or diagram form. Ability to deal with problems involving several concrete variables in standardized situations.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>SPECIAL QUALIFICATIONS<\u002Fb><\u002Fp> \n <p>Must be able to successfully pass a supervised welding test.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>PHYSICAL DEMANDS<\u002Fb> <b>The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<\u002Fb><\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p>While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to stand and use hands to finger, handle, or feel. The employee is occasionally required to walk; reach with hands and arms; stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl. The employee must frequently lift and\u002For move up to 25 pounds and occasionally lift and\u002For move up to 100 pounds. Specific vision abilities required by this job include color vision, peripheral vision, depth perception, and ability to adjust focus.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>WORK ENVIRONMENT<\u002Fb> <b>The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<\u002Fb><\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p>While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly exposed to moving mechanical parts and fumes or airborne particles. The employee is occasionally exposed to toxic or caustic chemicals, extreme heat, and vibration. The noise level in the work environment is usually loud.<\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p><b>TOOLS AND EQUIPMENT<\u002Fb> <b>The following tools and equipment are subject to be used by employees in the Welding Department.<\u002Fb><\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <p>Arc Welder Robot Welder<\u002Fp> \n <p>Plasma Torch Oxy\u002FAce Torch<\u002Fp> \n <p>Ding Hammer Adjustable Clamps<\u002Fp> \n <p>Deadblow Hammer Sander<\u002Fp> \n <p>Fixed Jigs Roll-over Jigs<\u002Fp> \n <p>Hydraulic Roll Over Jig Portable Grinders<\u002Fp> \n <p>Overhead Hoist<\u002Fp>\n <p><\u002Fp>\n <p><br> <\u002Fp>\n <div>\n  <b>Export Coordinator – Salina, KS<\u002Fb>\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <br> Great Plains Mfg is currently seeking an energetic \n  <b>Export Coordinator<\u002Fb> for our <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <br> This position works Monday through Thursday from 7:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. and Fridays from 7:00 a.m. to 11:00 a.m., with overtime as required, in our Corporate office in Salina, KS.\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <b><br> Essential Duties and Responsibilities:<\u002Fb>\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <ul>\n  <li> Work closely with Sales, Finance and Operations to maintain and update Freight. This individual will safely perform in-process inspections to monitor and evaluate manufacturing quality. requirements.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Perform special projects as requested and related tasks as needed.<\u002Fli>\n  <\u002Ful>\n  <p><b> Preferred Skills and Qualifications:<\u002Fb><\u002Fp>\n  <ul>\n Salina, KS. This position is an integral part of the organization’s Product Development Process and helps to design, test, and implement packaging designs.\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <br> This position works Monday through Thursday from 6:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. and reports to the Director of Facilities.\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <b><br> Primary Duties and Responsibilities:<\u002Fb>\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <ul>\n  <li> Oversee and manage complete packaging development process, including the creation of packaging designs, prototype development, and performance testing.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Troubleshoot new and existing packaging problems involving designs, materials and processes and provide creative, timely, and cost-effective solutions.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Analyze engineering drawings and specifications of product to determine physical characteristics of item, special handling, environmental and safety requirements, and types of materials required for packaging.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Manage multiple projects simultaneously.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Participate in product introduction teams, to deliver new products to market.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Identify and implement cost saving initiatives related to packaging materials, labor, efficiency, transportation, and storage.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Work closely with Engineering to optimize packaging supply base for cost, lead time, quality, regionalization, standardization, supply assurance, and compliance with customer, regulatory, and internal requirements.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Specify and recommend efficiency tools and test methods to develop and validate packaging designs.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Work with the manufacturing department to insure the packaging designs are optimized for manufacturability, including safety, quality, efficiency and cost considerations.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Develop and implement comprehensive test plans to ensure that packaging exceeds customer specifications.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Works in conjunction with the Manufacturing, Product Engineering, Purchasing, and Shipping departments.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Other duties may be assigned that require other qualifications, physical demands, and\u002For work environment.<\u002Fli>\n <\u002Ful>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <b><br> Required Skills and Qualifications:<\u002Fb>\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <ul>\n  <li> Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical or Packaging Engineering or 5 years of experience in manufacturing environment or a combination<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Must have 5+ years of experience in industrial or consumer packaging.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Knowledge and understanding of packaging design validation standards (ISO, ASTM, etc.), drafting and specification standards is essential.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Demonstrable proficiency in 3D CAD software is needed<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Problem solving and decision-making skills are necessary<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Must be able to work independently and as part of a Salina, KS.\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <br> The Senior Automation Engineer is responsible for day-to-day production support activities including but not limited to working with the operations group to identify and implement systems to help control the manufacturing processes. This role also leads the implementation of innovative technologies to help eliminate manufacturing defects and reduce cost. This position requires a hands-on person with an aptitude for problem solving and the ability to thrive in a production environment.\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <b><br> Primary Duties and Responsibilities:<\u002Fb>\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <ul>\n  <li> Lead collaborative discussions between leadership and key stakeholders to determine automation capabilities and goals<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Design and implement automated systems for use in diverse manufacturing and production environments<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Create and establish connections between information inputs, controllers and outputs<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Confer with vendors to determine product specifications and arrange for purchase of equipment, materials, or parts, and evaluate products according to specifications and quality standards for assigned projects<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Estimate project timelines, staffing requirements for project support, and related costs to provide information for management decisions<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Recommend methods for improving worker efficiency and reducing waste of materials and utilities through use of technology and lean manufacturing principles<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Support existing automation technology with component and process upgrades<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Assist in troubleshooting for defects or errors in technology<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Follow all Great Plains policies and OSHA safety regulations and wears prescribed safety and protective equipment.<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Other duties may be assigned that require other qualifications, physical demands, and\u002For work environment.<\u002Fli>\n <\u002Ful>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <b><br> Required Skills and Qualifications:<\u002Fb>\n <\u002Fdiv>\n <ul>\n  <li> Bachelor's degree in Mechanical or knowledge of process control systems, including Allen Bradley PLCs, HMIs, electrical drives, temperature, flow and pressure controls<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving skills in a fast-paced production environment<\u002Fli>\n  <li> Ability to excel in a team-oriented environment<\u002Fli>\n <\u002Ful>\n <div><\u002Fdiv>\n <div>\n  <br> At Great Plains Manufacturing, Now a Kubota company, Great Plains Manufacturing continues its dedication toward innovation and professional growth, while maintaining our family culture and community values. Grow with us! standardize.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Create hydraulic hardware and component specifications (i.e.: pumps, cylinders, valves plumbing, motors).<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Create hydraulic schematics and drawings.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Document and demonstrate solutions by developing documentation, flowcharts, and diagrams to support problem analysis.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Collaborate with all vehicle the project objectives for each program.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Complete complicated hydraulic system power consumption, component and circuit protection, flow rates, load and cooling requirements.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Collaborate with other members of the design team, test and evaluation, manufacturing, purchasing, quality control, etc. throughout the entire design process from concept generation to prototyping and production.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Create detailed design reports, 3D models and drawings based on Kubota standards<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Solve technical challenges related to new product design.<\u002Fli>\n  <\u002Ful>\n  <div><\u002Fdiv>\n  <div>\n   <b><br> Essential Skills and Qualifications<\u002Fb>\n  <\u002Fdiv>\n  <ul>\n   <li> Bachelor of Science degree and global team environment.\n  <\u002Fdiv>\n  <div><\u002Fdiv>\n  <div>\n   <b><br> Primary Duties and Responsibilities<\u002Fb>\n  <\u002Fdiv>\n  <ul>\n   <li> Design structures and mechanisms for for both stress and fatigue.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Generate new and creative designs for the structural and mechanical systems of Kubota CE products that meet requirements of quality, cost and delivery outlined in the project objectives for each program.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Design of welded, pinned and bolted structures.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Complete complicated system tolerance stack-ups.<\u002Fli>\n design.<\u002Fli>\n  <\u002Ful>\n  <div><\u002Fdiv>\n  <div>\n   <b><br> Essential Skills and Qualifications<\u002Fb>\n  <\u002Fdiv>\n  <ul>\n   <li> Bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering or product development experience<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Understanding of FEA analysis<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Experience and demonstrated success working in a cross-functional and cross-cultural environment<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Computer skills including MS Office, Google-based programs and 3D modeling<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Knowledge of manufacturing and fabrication processes such as cutting, <li> Availability to travel domestically and internationally as needed<\u002Fli>\n  <\u002Ful>\n  <div><\u002Fdiv>\n  <div>\n   <b><br> Preferred Skills and Experience<\u002Fb>\n  <\u002Fdiv>\n Engineer <\u002Fb>at our Abilene West facility in Abilene, KS.<\u002Fp>\n  <p> This position primarily works Monday - Thursday from 6:00 am to 4:30 pm.<\u002Fp>\n  <p><b> Primary Duties &amp; Responsibilities:<\u002Fb><\u002Fp>\n  <ul>\n   <li> Support manufacturing processes (assembly) with the primary focus being operator safety by studying product requirements; researching, designing, modifying, and testing methods.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Conceptualize and maintain plant layout and processes.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Spend time on the production floor assisting with process improvements, with main focus in assembly<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Assist in capital purchases and projects.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Read and interpret performance charts and graphs relating to safety, quality and productivity.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Design or spec fixtures, carts, tooling, etc.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Liaison between plant and product development to include submitting and managing engineering change requests.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Estimate production times, staffing requirements and related costs for management decisions.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Work closely with materials management to balance the flow of production through the plant.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Supports manufacturing to achieve safety, productivity and quality tats through process design, optimization projects and Kaizen initiatives.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Develop or revise standard operating and working practices.<\u002Fli>\n  <\u002Ful>\n  <p><\u002Fp>\n  <p><b><br> Preferred Skills &amp; Knowledge of manufacturing.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Lean advocate with demonstrated knowledge of manufacturing processes.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Knowledge of Microsoft Office Products.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Must be familiar with AutoCAD, 3D Solid Modeling and Creo.<\u002Fli>\n   <li> Excellent written and verbal communication skills.<\u002Fli>\n  <\u002Ful>\n  <p><br> At Great Plains our people make the Project Manager<\u002Fb><br>Great Plains Mfg is seeking an energetic, confident and detail-oriented person to join our team as a <b>Manufacturing Project Manager<\u002Fb>. The Project Manager will ensure the facilities are engaged early in the planning processes to increase production of current products and accept new product launches.<br>This position is an on-site role based in <b>Salina, KS<\u002Fb>. Primary work schedule is Monday through Thursday from 6:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Some day travel within the state of Kansas may be required. This position reports to the Director of Manufacturing.<br>*Primary Duties and Responsibilities: *<\u002Fp>\n<ul>\n <li>Systematically drive actions and accountability to required tasks and deliverables to the predetermined program timeline.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Drive \u002F coordinate the schedule for preproduction builds, power builds, prepare the plant for successful first time Run at Rate.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Ensure that all resources are in place to support the projects.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Document open issues, actions, owners and dates. Drive open issues to closure to accommodate rate launch.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Identify open issues, actions, owners and dates to review with leadership.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Coordinate with Procurement to ensure that purchased parts are properly defined and will be delivered as required.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Participate in the Plant Manager Staff meetings and share risks, needs and achievements.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Assures plant has all support needed from internal organization to launch plant\u002Fproduct successfully. Must eliminate any \"roadblocks\" which may hinder plant achieving goals.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Provide Plant Manager feedback on new staffing decisions and performance of plant staff personnel as necessary.<\u002Fli>\n <li>Other duties as assigned.<\u002Fli>\n<\u002Ful>\n<p>*Preferred Skills and Qualifications: *<\u002Fp>\n<ul>\n <li>Minimum 5 Years of Experience in a manufacturing environment is required<\u002Fli>\n <li>Manufacturing Project Management experience strongly preferred<\u002Fli>\n <li>Bachelor's degree in Engineering, Project Management or related field preferred<\u002Fli>\n <li>General understanding of manufacturing timelines<\u002Fli>\n <li>Functional discipline or operational leadership experience in a plant<\u002Fli>\n <li>Must have solid problem-solving skills<\u002Fli>\n <li>Strong computer skills with Microsoft Office, including Word, Excel, PowerPoint<\u002Fli>\n <li>Experience with fabrication, welding, paint, and assembly helpful<\u002Fli>\n<\u002Ful>\n<p>At Great Plains Manufacturing, our people make the difference, making our Company a great place to work and grow.
